        Determine the vertical alignment of the contents of a table cell

        according to [MS-DOC], v20140721, 2.9.341

        If the text is also rotated (i.e. setTextRotation() also applies) the alignment sometimes leads to strange results. But thats purely a rendering issue and since text-rotation is

        • only used sparingly
        • a cutting edge CSS-feature, which barely becomes rendered at the moment, anyways
        we do not investigate further here.

        Mixes two colors into one.

        Note: This does try to do something useful with the ipat, but it does not resemble the original formatting that Word would apply. It only makes different combinations of (color#1, color#2, ipat) distinguishable.
